entries.title: Elon Musk Says Saudi Fund Wanted to Take Tesla Private
entries.description: Mr. Musk is testifying in a lawsuit filed by investors who claim that his statements about a plan to take Tesla private in 2018 caused them to lose billions of dollars.

entries.title: Supreme Court Puts Off Considering State Laws Curbing Internet Platforms
entries.description: The laws, enacted by Florida and Texas in response to conservative complaints about censorship, have been challenged under the First Amendment.

entries.title: Microsoft Extends Multibillion-Dollar Deal With Creator of ChatGPT
entries.description: The tech giant aims to to remain at the forefront of generative artificial intelligence with its partnership with OpenAI.

entries.title: Spotify to Lay Off 6% of Its Work Force
entries.description: The audio streaming platform becomes the latest big technology company to cut costs over worries about the economy.

entries.title: Tech Layoffs Continue as Shares Fall and Interest Rates Rise
entries.description: Rock-bottom rates were the secret engine fueling $1 billion start-ups and virtual attempts to conquer the physical world. But in 2023, reality bites.
